<subSubSection id="52BB49D6FF92FF83B6B7FE9EA7F1FE1D" pageId="4" pageNumber="239" type="description">
<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF92FF83B6B7FE9EA61CFE7D" blockId="4.[170,1229,330,453]" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">
D i a g n o s i s. This species is characterized by the abundant red and yellow coloration of body; the granulate propodeum and first metasomal tergite (
<figureCitation id="829A06D8FF92FF83B505FEBEA7DFFE5D" box="[877,938,362,389]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1766,1788]" captionTargetBox="[272,1126,1043,1744]" captionTargetId="figure-372@4.[272,1126,1043,1744]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Perithous spp.: 1 — P. speculator, female, habitus, lateral view; 2 — P. scurra, female, dorsal view of the second metasomal tergite; 3–4 — dorsal view of propodeum and metasomal tergites I–II, female: 3 — P. divinator; 4 — P. septemcinctorius; 5 — P. scurra, male, habitus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454728" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454728/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="28D5C64FFF92FF83B5DDFEBEA7B6FE5C" box="[949,963,362,388]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">4</emphasis>
); the ovipositor which is about 5.9–7.2 × length of hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1A1E1A5DFF92FF83B6B7FE7EA7F1FE1D" blockId="4.[170,1229,330,453]" box="[223,900,426,453]" pageId="4" pageNumber="239">Flight period in Carpathians. July to August (2.07–19.08).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
